definition.value: An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose and beta-D-mannopyranose joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond.

A branched amino hexasaccharide compound consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a Man-alpha(1->3)-[Man-alpha(1->6)]-Man-beta(1->4)-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and a Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.
